Run 2127

24 Nov 2019: Fox & Goose, Greywell, by Squiffy


 

Even before the run the RA was in trouble with the landlady of The Fox and Goose for parking in the wrong place - not once but twice! The runners made a false start looking in vain for the sawdust up The Street south from The Fox and Goose car park, before discovering the true trail up Deptford Lane. Then most of the trail was through muddy, muddy, leaf-strewn, muddy forest tracks. We passed one end of the Greywell canal tunnel. A sparsity of sawdust meant we spent some time searching for the trail from time to time. Even so, the runners were back in under an hour and had at least 10 minutes to wait before the first of the walkers returned. After the down-downs we had fun pushing a (non hasher) car out of the muddy field beyond the pub car park.

Run 2125 - AGM RUN

10 Nov 2019 at 10:30am, Woodlands Walk, Farnborough, 'Er Indoors & Hobble


 

Hobble announced he would buy any of the runners a beer if they came back with dry shoes so we knew we wouldn't. But the sun was shining. The run started with a fastish romp through woodlands, dry enough underfoot considering the rain we'd had, then through some roads and back for the wet part. With waterproof socks proving how well they held the water IN, we returned to the car park in 45-55 minutes for down-downs (Including birthday hashers Little Prick and - belatedly - Yorkie) and hence to the Gurkha Palace for an excellent buffet followed by the AGM.

Run 2096

50 Years of U.K. Hashing

A historic trail laid by Mountain Rescue close to the 1st U.K. Hash trail which he laid 50 years ago. 

Hippo explained that MR had been posted from the Far East, where he had enjoyed hashing, to the Royal Corps of Transport where he played with trains. Here he managed to persuade a bunch of chaps (no women) to follow a hash trail that he had laid in whitewash at Longmoor Inclosure. Subsequent trails were laid with one inch paper squares because the whitewash proved unsatisfactory. Hashes initially cost two shillings, which was enough to pay for the beer. MR was subsequently posted to Germany where he started a German hash. 

Yellow Peril brought along two home-made cakes to enjoy before the down downs. MR was then presented with an engraved hip flask full of rum, a bottle of port and two bags of flour, all in a rucksack, while we stood in a circle being attacked by midges. 

Petal: Excellent Run - perfect celebration of MR's 50 years of hashing. 

Dodo: Nice to have an original Founder of our hash! We are very lucky!

Charmaine Chardonnay: Lovely! Congratulations. Nice cake. Nice run. Nice company. Horrible mosquitoes.
